[h1]QoL - Medical Icons[/h1]

[b]SERVER-SIDE mod. The host must be subscribed.[/b]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]What this mod does[/h2]

QoL - Medical Icons replaces vanilla Barotrauma medical item icons and sprites with clearer custom visuals.

The goal is simple: medical items should be readable at a glance. Instead of a pile of nearly identical syringes, items are grouped into recognizable visual classes and then separated further by color and status-affliction marks.

[h2]Visual groups[/h2]

[list]
[*][b]Medicine[/b] - core medical chemicals and general treatment items.
[*][b]Basic chemicals[/b] - utility medical ingredients.
[*][b]Toxins[/b] - harmful substances and poison syringes.
[*][b]Antidotes[/b] - vial-style counteragents.
[*][b]Stimulants[/b] - injector-style performance drugs.
[/list]

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]

[list]
[*]Works best with mods that do not override the same vanilla medical items.
[*]If another mod changes vanilla medical items, load order may decide which textures appear.
[*]Other local mods can be edited manually to point their item textures to this mod.
[/list]

[h2]Notes[/h2]

[list]
[*]This mod changes visuals only. It does not rebalance medicine, afflictions, crafting, talents, or item behavior.
[*]The host needs the mod enabled. Clients do not need to subscribe separately when joining a hosted game.
[*]Designed to keep the Barotrauma medical style while making item recognition faster.
[/list]

